# Phase 1: Analyze the Fix

This is a patch for IVDescriptors, LoopVectorize:

Reland "[LV] Support conditional scalar assignments of masked operations"
This patch extends the support added in #158088 to loops where the assignment is non-speculatable (e.g. a conditional load or divide).

For example, the following loop can now be vectorized:

```
int simple_csa_int_load(
  int* a, int* b, int default_val, int N, int threshold)
{
  int result = default_val;
  for (int i = 0; i < N; ++i)
    if (a[i] > threshold)
      result = b[i];
  return result;
}
```

It does this by extending the recurrence matching from only looking for selects, to include phis where all operands are the header phi, except for one which can be an arbitrary value outside the recurrence.

---

Reverts llvm/llvm-project#180275 (original PR: #178862)

Additional type legalization for `ISD::VECTOR_FIND_LAST_ACTIVE` was added in #180290, which should resolve the backend crashes on x86. 
